                    <comment id="12380389" author="olegk" created="Sat, 3 May 2003 02:41:21 +0100"  >Mike,&lt;br/&gt;
I do not particularly like the fact that the input string has to converted to an&lt;br/&gt;
array of char only to be converted back to a string the very next moment. I&lt;br/&gt;
guess we should provide an additional constructor for the URI class. &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Besides, I find URI constructors a bit odd. Is there any particular reason why&lt;br/&gt;
escaped uri should be passed as an array of chars, whereas unescaped uri should&lt;br/&gt;
be passed as strings, and not visa versa? It&amp;#39;s too late to change anything about&lt;br/&gt;
it. I just find it weird.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Oleg</comment>
                    <comment id="12380390" author="becke@u.washington.edu" created="Sat, 3 May 2003 03:16:07 +0100"  >I agree, it is strange.  Seems like a flag would be more appropriate.  Perhaps&lt;br/&gt;
someone will tackle URI for our 2.X release.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Mike</comment>
